Act 643 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1854
4
5 By: Representative Bentley
6 By: Senator Flippo
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO EXEMPT A HOME CAREGIVER FROM HOME CAREGIVER
10 TRAINING IF HE OR SHE PREVIOUSLY COMPLETED TRAINING;
11 AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
12
13
Subtitle
14
15 TO EXEMPT A HOME CAREGIVER FROM HOME
16 CAREGIVER TRAINING IF HE OR SHE
17 PREVIOUSLY COMPLETED TRAINING.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
20
21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 20-77-2304 is amended to read as follows:
22 20-77-2304. Exemptions.
23 An individual may provide caregiver services without the training
24 required under this subchapter if the person is a:
25 (1) Certified Nursing Assistant;
26 (2) Licensed practical nurse;
27 (3) Parent, grandparent, child, grandchild, or sibling of the
28 recipient of the services;
29 (4) Physician;
30 (5) Registered nurse;
31 (6) Service provider who does not receive compensation for his
32 or her services;
33 (7) Licensed social worker;
34 (8) Court-appointed legal guardian of the recipient of the
35 caregiver services; or
36 (9) A direct-care worker providing caregiver services to a
*JMB569*
